        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Release idle WebViews on memory pressure",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add a macOS memory-pressure monitor for warning and critical pressure events.\n- Evict only idle cached OpenAI dashboard WebViews when pressure arrives, preserving active dashboard refreshes.\n- Run malloc pressure relief alongside the WebView cache cleanup.\n\n## Proof\n\n- Real local before profile, installed CodexBar 0.36.1 with trace logging: main app idle averaged 0.152% CPU and 30.6 MB RSS, while the associated WebKit WebContent process held a 306.1 MB physical footprint with a 541.7 MB peak after dashboard work. Samples were idle/mach_msg dominated, pointing to retained WebKit memory rather than a Swift CPU loop.\n- After-fix app-path proof added in `426d7b8a`: `Memory pressure monitor evicts idle shared WebViews without interrupting busy WebViews` seeds the shared dashboard WebView cache with one idle entry and one busy entry, runs the `MemoryPressureMonitor` warning handler, and proves the idle WebView is evicted while the busy WebView remains cached.\n- `swift test --filter OpenAIDashboardWebViewCacheTests`: 19 tests passed after 2.022 seconds. The focused run emitted the monitor log line `warning com.steipete.codexbar.memory-pressure: level=warning [CodexBarCore] System memory pressure` during the new after-fix test.\n- The PR branch app was also packaged and launched from `/Users/alec/Dev/CodexBar/CodexBar.app/Contents/MacOS/CodexBar`. A local `sudo /usr/bin/memory_pressure -S -l warn` / `critical` simulation attempt did not produce CodexBar unified-log entries in this environment, so the PR proof relies on the deterministic app-path test above rather than overclaiming OS delivery evidence.\n- `.build/lint-tools/bin/swiftformat Sources Tests --lint`: 0/1140 files require formatting.\n- `.build/lint-tools/bin/swiftlint --strict`: 0 violations in 1139 files.\n- `swift build --build-tests`: passed.\n- `git diff --check`: passed.\n- `make check`: locally blocked before Swift lint by the existing `node --check docs/site.js` ESM mismatch under Node v25.9.0; the checked `upstream/main:docs/site.js` starts with an ESM import as well, so this is not introduced by this patch.",
